1. Check if the tree is empty.
2. Search for the node to be deleted in the tree.
3. If the node is not found, terminate the function.
4. If the node is found, check if it has any children.
5. If the node has no children, simply remove it from the tree.
6. If the node has one child, replace it with its child.
7. If the node has two children, find the minimum value in its right subtree.
8. Replace the node to be deleted with the minimum value found in step 7.
9. Delete the minimum value from its original place in the right subtree.

